    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-12T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="1296"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1296">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123 Ei 6/101</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The</hi>
                    <gloss type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                    </gloss>
                    <hi rend="italic">to the Minister in Roumania, Servia, and Bulgaria</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_VCJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Vopicka</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-12T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1915, 4 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>191. For your information and for <persName corresp="#p_EL1"
                        >Einstein</persName>:<quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Your 3, November 8. Department has no authority without special act of
                            Congress to appoint Charge d’Affaires, inasmuch as such appointment
                            would in fact establish new mission. You may, however, as special agent
                            continue to enjoy individual rank of Chargé d’Affaires with the
                            distinction that you hold no office as such.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
